{"parse":{"title":"Pages for Peace","pageid":27888151,"revid":792925275,"text":{"*":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><p><i><b>Pages for Peace</b></i> is a book created as an after school enrichment program by the <a href=\"/wiki/Groton-Dunstable_Regional_Middle_School\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Groton-Dunstable Regional Middle School\">Groton-Dunstable Regional Middle School</a> in <a href=\"/wiki/Groton,_Massachusetts\" title=\"Groton, Massachusetts\">Groton, Massachusetts</a>.  The group created the second largest book in the world (by physical dimensions).  The subject of the book they have chosen to create is <a href=\"/wiki/World_Peace\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"World Peace\">World Peace</a>. This enrichment program was created by 5th grade teacher <a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Betsy_Sawyer&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1\" class=\"new\" title=\"Betsy Sawyer (page does not exist)\">Betsy Sawyer</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Pages_1-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Pages-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>  <i>Pages for Peace</i> consists of recollections and reflections on the topic of World Peace from people all over the world.\n</p>\n<div id=\"toc\" class=\"toc\"><input type=\"checkbox\" role=\"button\" id=\"toctogglecheckbox\" class=\"toctogglecheckbox\" style=\"display:none\" /><div class=\"toctitle\" lang=\"en\" dir=\"ltr\"><h2>Contents</h2><span class=\"toctogglespan\"><label class=\"toctogglelabel\" for=\"toctogglecheckbox\"></label></span></div>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-1\"><a href=\"#History\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">History</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-2\"><a href=\"#Notable_contributors\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Notable contributors</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-3\"><a href=\"#Size\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Size</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-4\"><a href=\"#References\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">4</span> <span class=\"toctext\">References</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"History\">History</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Pages_for_Peace&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" title=\"Edit section: History\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>In October 2004 eight <a href=\"/wiki/5th_grade\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"5th grade\">5th grade</a> students joined Pages for Peace becoming its first members.\n</p><p>In late 2007 members of Pages for Peace visited The <a href=\"/wiki/University_of_Massachusetts_Lowell\" title=\"University of Massachusetts Lowell\">University of Massachusetts Lowell</a> to create the page turner for the book.\n</p><p>In September 2008 members of Pages for Peace visited the <a href=\"/wiki/United_Nations\" title=\"United Nations\">United Nations</a> headquarters in <a href=\"/wiki/New_York_City\" title=\"New York City\">New York City</a> to give a presentation to the annual international youth conference, and have been invited back every year since (as of 2016).<sup id=\"cite_ref-Pages_1-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Pages-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>In June 2010, <i>Pages for Peace</i> was awarded the Peace Abbey's \"Courage of Conscience\" award, which had previously been awarded to <a href=\"/wiki/Mother_Teresa\" title=\"Mother Teresa\">Mother Teresa</a> and the <a href=\"/wiki/Dalai_Lama\" title=\"Dalai Lama\">Dalai Lama</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>The group received the honor of meeting and speaking with the <a href=\"/wiki/United_Nations\" title=\"United Nations\">United Nations</a> Secretary-General <a href=\"/wiki/Ban_Ki-moon\" title=\"Ban Ki-moon\">Ban Ki-moon</a> in 2015, a decade into the project.\n</p><p>In October 2014, <i>Pages for Peace</i> went to the <a href=\"/wiki/John_F._Kennedy_Presidential_Library_and_Museum\" title=\"John F. Kennedy Presidential Library and Museum\">John F. Kennedy Presidential Library and Museum</a> to begin its world tour, and the event even featured a personal video message of the <a href=\"/wiki/United_Nations\" title=\"United Nations\">United Nations</a> Secretary-General Ban-Ki Moon.\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Notable_contributors\">Notable contributors</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Pages_for_Peace&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" title=\"Edit section: Notable contributors\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>Among the contributors to the <i>Pages for Peace</i> project have been:\n</p>\n<ul><li>The <a href=\"/wiki/Dalai_Lama\" title=\"Dalai Lama\">Dalai Lama</a> <sup id=\"cite_ref-Boston_3-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Boston-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup></li>\n<li><a href=\"/wiki/IAEA\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"IAEA\">IAEA</a> Director General <a href=\"/wiki/Mohamed_ElBaradei\" title=\"Mohamed ElBaradei\">Mohamed ElBaradei</a><sup id=\"cite_ref-4\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup></li>\n<li>Former United States President <a href=\"/wiki/Jimmy_Carter\" title=\"Jimmy Carter\">Jimmy Carter</a><sup id=\"cite_ref-Boston_3-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Boston-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup></li>\n<li>Former South African President <a href=\"/wiki/Nelson_Mandela\" title=\"Nelson Mandela\">Nelson Mandela</a><sup id=\"cite_ref-Boston_3-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Boston-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup></li>\n<li>United Nations ambassador <a href=\"/wiki/Anwarul_Chowdhury\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Anwarul Chowdhury\">Anwarul Chowdhury</a> <sup id=\"cite_ref-Pages_1-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Pages-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup></li>\n<li>Skateboarder <a href=\"/wiki/Tony_Hawk\" title=\"Tony Hawk\">Tony Hawk</a> <sup id=\"cite_ref-Pages_1-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Pages-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup></li>\n<li>Retired US General <a href=\"/wiki/Peter_Pace\" title=\"Peter Pace\">Peter Pace</a> <sup id=\"cite_ref-Pages_1-4\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Pages-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup></li></ul>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Size\">Size</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Pages_for_Peace&amp;action=edit&amp;section=3\" title=\"Edit section: Size\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<ul><li>The Book is 12 feet tall and 20 feet wide open-face.</li>\n<li>The Book contains over 535 double sided pages.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Pages_1-5\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Pages-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup></li>\n<li>The Book weighs over a ton.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Boston_3-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Boston-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup></li></ul>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Pages_for_Peace&amp;action=edit&amp;section=4\" title=\"Edit section: References\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-Pages-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\">^ <a href=\"#cite_ref-Pages_1-0\"><sup><i><b>a</b></i></sup></a> <a href=\"#cite_ref-Pages_1-1\"><sup><i><b>b</b></i></sup></a> <a href=\"#cite_ref-Pages_1-2\"><sup><i><b>c</b></i></sup></a> <a href=\"#cite_ref-Pages_1-3\"><sup><i><b>d</b></i></sup></a> <a href=\"#cite_ref-Pages_1-4\"><sup><i><b>e</b></i></sup></a> <a href=\"#cite_ref-Pages_1-5\"><sup><i><b>f</b></i></sup></a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.pagesforpeace.org/home.html\">Pages for Peace Website</a></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-2\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-2\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation news\">Sato, Hiroko (27 June 2010). <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.lowellsun.com/ci_15388782?source=most_emailed\">\"<span style=\"padding-left:0.2em;\">'</span>Pages of Peace' turn into big honor\"</a>. <i><a href=\"/wiki/Lowell_Sun\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Lowell Sun\">Lowell Sun</a></i><span class=\"reference-accessdate\">. Retrieved <span class=\"nowrap\">30 June</span> 2010</span>.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.jtitle=Lowell+Sun&amp;rft.atitle=%27Pages+of+Peace%27+turn+into+big+honor&amp;rft.date=2010-06-27&amp;rft.aulast=Sato&amp;rft.aufirst=Hiroko&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.lowellsun.com%2Fci_15388782%3Fsource%3Dmost_emailed&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3APages+for+Peace\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-Boston-3\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\">^ <a href=\"#cite_ref-Boston_3-0\"><sup><i><b>a</b></i></sup></a> <a href=\"#cite_ref-Boston_3-1\"><sup><i><b>b</b></i></sup></a> <a href=\"#cite_ref-Boston_3-2\"><sup><i><b>c</b></i></sup></a> <a href=\"#cite_ref-Boston_3-3\"><sup><i><b>d</b></i></sup></a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation news\">Dyer, John (1 June 2008). <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.boston.com/news/local/articles/2008/06/01/epic_ambition/?page=1\">\"Epic ambition: Dream of a 1-ton book on peace drives Groton-Dunstable club\"</a>. <i><a href=\"/wiki/Boston_Globe\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Boston Globe\">Boston Globe</a></i><span class=\"reference-accessdate\">. Retrieved <span class=\"nowrap\">30 June</span> 2010</span>.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%